+## Python Environment (Critical — Prevent False "Missing Dependencies" Errors)
+
+**Rule: Every Python command MUST be prefixed with `uv run`.**
+
+This project uses `uv` with a workspace `.venv` (Python 3.13). Running bare `python`, `pytest`, or `pip` hits the system Python (3.11, Homebrew) which has different — usually missing — packages. This produces false "ModuleNotFoundError" that wastes hours.
+
+**Correct:**
+```bash
+uv run pytest tests/
+uv run python script.py
+uv run pip list
+```
+
+**Wrong (will fail or use wrong env):**
+```bash
+python -m pytest tests/       # ❌ uses system Python 3.11, not .venv 3.13
+pytest tests/                 # ❌ same — might hit system pytest
+pip install something         # ❌ installs to wrong env
+```
+
+**Verification before running any Python command:**
+```bash
+uv run python -c "import opentelemetry.trace; print('venv OK')"
+```
+
+**Why this matters:** The system has Python 3.11 at `/opt/homebrew/bin/python`. The project `.venv` has Python 3.13 with all deps. Running bare `python` silently uses the wrong interpreter. The error `ModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'opentelemetry'` with `981 tests un-runnable` happened because an agent ran `python -m pytest tests/` instead of `uv run pytest tests/`.
+
 ## Naming Conventions (Critical — Prevent Future Symlinks)
 
 **Problem prevented**: `spine-api/` (hyphen) vs `spine_api` (underscore) required a symlink because Python imports need underscores. This is pre-launch — no backward compat needed.
